** SGAuto **

* What is it:
    This is a program that lets you monitor and automatically backup selected files if they were modified.
    It can be used for savegame backup but also for any other file(s) you need to monitor and backup instantly
    if they change.

* Why is it:
    Because those pesky developers think, that they know better how I want to play my game.
    So few years back (for FTL afair) I wrote simple script to backup it's save file.
    Then program grew, when I needed something new from it.
    And here you have current version I decided to release into the wild.
    I will update it when i feel like it, probably when I need a new feature for some game.

* How to use it:
    If you have Python3 with PyQt5, then you can just copy sgauto.py, sgauto.ui and sgauto.ico to any directory and start it with "python sgauto.py".
    For Windows you can use provided exe file. It's just bundled version with pyinstaller.

    After program starts select file(s) you want to monitor. Then select folder for backup files.
    Finaly press Start. It will save default config and start monitoring your files.
    If change is detected it will zip all files into backup directory.

* Plugin comments:
    SGAuto supports automatic comment extraction via Python plugin.
    When a backup is created, a plugin can read from your monitored files and generate a comment string.

    To use:
    1. Create a Python file with an extract_comment(file_path, all_files, log) function
       (file_path is file you attach your script to)
    2. Attach your plugin to one of files in monitored list
    3. The plugin is called automatically on each backup

    See example_plugin.py for a working example.

Get latest version at: https://github.com/misiektw/sgauto
